\n<li data-start=\"2802\" data-end=\"2858\"><code data-start=\"2804\" data-end=\"2813\">SIGUSR2</code>: Toggle logging/debugging modes dynamically.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"2860\" data-end=\"2941\">Since both are user-defined, <strong data-start=\"2889\" data-end=\"2935\">you decide how they behave in your program</strong>! ðŸš€</p>\n<p data-start=\"2943\" data-end=\"3044\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">Would you like an example where a process <strong data-start=\"2985\" data-end=\"3040\">toggles between two modes using SIGUSR1 and SIGUSR2</strong>? ðŸ˜Š</p></div>"
